s\nupon the shoulders of the\nteachers of the South\u2014in the\npulpit and in the class-room.\nBut the compensation ac\ncorded the great majority of\nthem is inadequate.\nThe Southern Railway Sys\ntem, which pays three million\ndollars per annum in school\ntaxes, voices not only its own\nbest interest but the ambition\nof its \u20ac0,000 employees in re\nspect to the future of their\nchildren and their section,\nwhen it expresses the view that\ngreater rewards should be of\nfered the men and women who\nare building Southern citizen\nship of tomorrow.\nV.\n.X\nA\ny\nvJL,;\ne SOUTHERN SERVES THE SOUTH\n'f 1\nr.\n<\u00abr\n4'\ni\nv:'j\ni\n.1\n&amm\niit id 'mAaS olMbJb'i\nOver sboe fsior*\n(X)L(JUBU, b. C.\npuoan so, tin\nWANT ADS\nIVANTED^Poplar, Ash and Cypress\nstanding timber. Will figure with\nyou on any size tract. Give full de\ntails in first letter. Hou'man^Lum\nbei\u2018 Company, Columbia, S. C.\ni\u2019OR SALE OR RENTp\u2014.My place at\nChapin, S. C. Address J. J. \u00a9ick\nley, Granite Falls, N. C.\nkVANTED\u2014Men or women to take\norders for genuine guaranteed hos\niery for men, women and children;\neliminate gaming. Salary, $75 a\nweek full time; $1.50 an hour spare\ntime. Cottons, heathers, silk. In\nternational Stocking Mills, Norris\ntown, Pa.\nTRESPASS NOTICE.\nThis' is to notify all persons not to\nHunt or trespass in any way whatever\nan our premises, as the law will posi\ntively be. enforced against all tres\npassers.\nT. S. SEA^fe.\nA. V. SEAia.\nTRESPASS NOTICE.\nAll persons are hereby warned not\nto trespass on the lands of the un\ndersigned by-hunting or in any other\nmanner whatsoever, under the strict\npenalty of the lawi.\nGeorge F. Taylor.\nTRESPASS NOTICE.\nThis is to notify all persons\u2019 not to\n:huiilfr<iV trespass in any manner what\n'soever upon our lands.\n1,f Vernice Berry.\nR. L. Berry.-\nDee.' 30.1U23.\nNOTICE OF APPLICATION\nFOR FINAL DISCHARGE.\nNotice is given that on January 26,\n1924, at 11 o\u2019clock a. m\u201e I wil